\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Such is the function of the concept of evil\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to give glamour, in both meanings of the word, to our lives. Pain, on the other hand, is an unglamorous fact of life and cannot be raised or lowered to the status of a concept, either moral or metaphysical, and compresses the distance between the condition of being and the condition of suffering. In pain, the two are one. For a Western religion such as Christianity, evil can be brushed aside as being \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93in the world\u8221\'94 but not identical with it, offering believers the possibility of atoning for their divagations from the straight and narrow, and, if all goes well, securing their eternal salvation.\~ }
